description:
&lt;p&gt;Caring. Compassionate. Skilled. Meticulous. Enthusiastic.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These are just some of the words that we’d used to describe the world-class nurses at Great Ormond Street Hospital (GOSH).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for Band 5 nurses to join our ICU unit; NICU.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome applications from both Child and Adult registered nurses with experience in the field or those who would like to consider a change in their career to this exciting specialty. We offer a fantastic world class education programme which will help you develop your specialist knowledge and skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Providing family centred care to your patients you will plan, deliver, assess and evaluate your treatments, ensuring children and their families remain at the heart of every decision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will benefit from extensive development opportunities. These include a comprehensive foundation in Paediatric Cardiac Nursing and Intensive Care Nursing that leads onto a structured development pathway which will give you the tools and skills to progress into senior nursing roles within the specialty.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information on our ICU wards, please refer to the ICU ward information document.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Along with taking your nursing skills to the next level in a hospital with an international reputation in the heart of London, you will also enjoy a raft of staff benefits including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expert support and education programmes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interest free season ticket loan&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Staff accommodation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS pension scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cycle to work scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Health and social wellbeing schemes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We believe in offering flexibility and part time hours will be considered where they can be accommodated.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Amy Gilbert (Ward Sister) - amy.gilbert@gosh.nhs.uk. Tel: 020 7405 9200 Ext. 8812&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
